1.	Download the Ubuntu iso (desktop not server) 
2.	Run vmware , you’ll see something like this:

3.	Select “Create a New Virtual Machine”
4.	Select “Installer disc image file” and browse to the Ubuntu iso 
5.	Enter name, create username and password and hit next
6.	Select the maximum disk size and type
7.	This brings you to the confirmation page. Click “Customize Hardware”
8.	In the hardware options section select the amount of memory you want the VM to use.  We used 20gigs
9.	This brings you back to the confirmation page. Click Finish 
10.	 Wait for install
11.	 Enter Login and password at prompt
